title: VSS Unity preparing for first powered flight since Branson’s trip in 2021
summary: After a nearly two-year pause in flights, starting after a deviation from controlled airspace during Sir Richard Branson’s flight in July 2021, the Virgin Galactic SpaceShipTwo VSS Unity is being prepared to make its first powered flight since the eventful Unity 22 mission.

title: Virgin Galactic attempts final test flight before beginning ticketed space trips
summary: Virgin Galactic is preparing to launch its first spaceflight in nearly two years on Thursday, as the space tourism company aims to pass a final test before flying commercial passengers.

title: At long last, the glorious future we were promised in space is on the way
summary: "It is gratifying to see folks coming around."

title: First components of Mobile Launcher 2 arrive at KSC
summary: The first components for a new mobile launch platform for NASA’s Space Launch System, which has suffered extensive cost and schedule overruns, have arrived at the Kennedy Space Center.

title: Iceye introduces Dwell imaging mode
summary: Iceye unveiled an imaging mode at the GEOINT Symposium that distinguishes human-made from natural objects and highlights moving vehicles.
